<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3560] the hbase-default entry of &quot;hbase.defaults.for.version&quot; causes tests not to run via not-maven</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3560</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;using the default setup of a maven project for intellij, tests fail because the hbase-default.xml contains a token @@@VERSION@@@.  The maven build creates a substitute file, but this file isn&apos;t by default on the classpath.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a different place to put the hbase-default.xml file than target/classes?  That is excluded from the classpath because IJ has it&apos;s own compiler. Including that path in the project classpath seems dangerous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we get the output to go to just &apos;target&apos; or &apos;target/generated-sources/org&apos; perhaps?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
